        "Do not assume rules from your origin state apply. Rules vary across state, local, and federal jurisdictions. Verify directly with official sources.": "勿好假设侬出发州个规则适用。各州、地方搭联邦司法管辖区个规则不一样。请直接向官方来源核实。",
        "Do not characterize voter registration by non-citizens using legal-conclusion or accusatory language. Use neutral framing such as 'generally not eligible' and 'may create immigration complications'. Direct readers to consult a licensed immigration attorney. Do not give procedural advice for any specific state.": "勿用法律结论或者指控性措辞来描述非公民个选民登记。请用中性表述,例如「一般勿具备资格」搭「可能给移民事项带来复杂问题」。引导读者咨询持证移民律师。勿对任何具体州提供程序建议。",
        "Do not characterize whether any visa category can establish residency in a specific state as a determination. Frame as classification rules to verify with the school registrar and the state higher-education agency. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "勿用判定个方式陈述某签证类别在某州是否好建立居住身份。请按要向学校教务处搭州高等教育机构核实个分类规则来表述。请遵循 SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Do not determine residency. List factors to verify. Direct to the relevant agency or school.": "勿认定居住身份。列出要核实个因素。引导到相关机构或者学校。",
        "Do not determine that a household 'is' or 'is not' eligible for Medicaid. Frame as items to verify with the state Medicaid agency. Use 'may apply' and 'rules differ by jurisdiction'. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "勿判定家庭是否符合 Medicaid 资格。请按要向州 Medicaid 机构核实个事项来表述。请使用「可能适用」搭「各司法管辖区个规则不一样」。请遵循 SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Do not list which states grant in-state tuition for DACA recipients. Frame as classification rules to verify with the school registrar and the state higher-education agency.": "勿列出哪些州对 DACA 受益人给予本州学费待遇。请按要向学校教务处搭州高等教育机构核实个分类规则来表述。",
        "Do not provide a public-charge determination or say that using benefits 'will' or 'will not' affect immigration. Frame as 'may interact' and recommend consulting a licensed immigration attorney. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "勿就「公共负担」作判定,也勿陈述使用福利「会」或「勿会」影响移民事项。请用「可能产生相互作用」,并建议咨询持证移民律师。请遵循 SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Do not provide medical or transport instructions for controlled substances.": "勿就管制药品提供医疗或者运输方面个具体指引。",
        "Do not provide tactical instructions for transporting, possessing, hiding, storing, modifying, or avoiding enforcement for regulated items.": "勿就受管制物品个运输、持有、藏匿、储存、改装,或规避执法提供具体操作指引。",
        "Do not provide tax advice. Direct to official tax agency and qualified professionals.": "勿提供税务建议。请引导到官方税务机构搭合格专业人士。",
        "Do not provide tax advice. Direct to state tax agency or qualified tax professional.": "勿提供税务建议。引导到州税务机构或者合格税务专业人士。",
        "Do not say a Board of Nursing in a particular state grants or refuses an applicant's NCLEX path. Use 'verify with the destination Board of Nursing'. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "勿陈述某州护理委员会是否批准或拒绝申请人个 NCLEX 路径。请用「向目的州护理委员会核实」介种措辞。请遵循 SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Do not say a particular aid program 'is open to' or 'is closed to' DACA recipients or LPRs. Use 'verify with the state aid agency and the school financial-aid office'. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "勿陈述某助学项目「对 DACA 受益人 / LPR 开放」或「关闭」。请用「向州助学机构搭学校助学办公室核实」介种措辞。请遵循 SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Do not say a person 'can' or 'cannot' enroll. Use 'verify current eligibility categories with the marketplace operator' since federal rules have changed. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "勿陈述某人「好」或「勿好」参保。请用「向市场运营方核实当前资格类别」,因为联邦规则已经发生变化。请遵循 SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Do not state how a specific state defines residency for a given visa category or that someone 'is' a resident. Frame as 'rules differ by jurisdiction' and 'verify with the destination-state tax agency'. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "勿陈述某州对某签证类别如何定义居住身份,也勿陈述某人「是」居民。请用「各司法管辖区个规则不一样」搭「向目的州税务机构核实」。请遵循 SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Do not state how a specific state defines residency or that someone 'is' a resident. Frame as 'rules differ by jurisdiction' and 'verify with the destination-state tax agency'. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "勿陈述某州如何定义居住身份,也勿陈述某人「是」居民。请用「各司法管辖区个规则不一样」搭「向目的州税务机构核实」。请遵循 SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Do not state that any specific board does or does not license a given visa category. Frame everything as items to verify with the destination-state board. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "勿陈述任何具体委员会对某签证类别是否发执照。一律按要向目的州委员会核实个事项来表述。请遵循 SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Do not state that any specific board does or does not license non-citizens. Frame everything as items to verify with the destination-state board. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "勿陈述任何具体委员会对非公民是否发执照。一律按要向目的州委员会核实个事项来表述。请遵循 SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Do not state that any specific person is or is not required to register. Frame as a federal requirement that 'may apply' depending on age and sex, with state implementation details to verify. Use neutral language and follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "勿陈述任何具体个人是否要登记。请按联邦要求来表述,根据年龄搭性别可能适用,州一级实施细节要核实。请用中性措辞,并遵循 SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Do not state whether the user is eligible for licensure. Only identify requirements to verify.": "勿陈述用户是否具备执业资格。仅列出要核实个要求。",
        "Do not state which states do or do not issue licenses to a given group, and do not list specific accepted documents. Frame everything as items to verify with the destination-state DMV.": "勿陈述哪些州对特定群体发或勿发驾照,也勿列出具体接受个证件。一律按要向目的州 DMV 核实个事项来表述。",
        "Do not state which states issue or do not issue licenses to a given visa category, and do not list specific accepted documents. Frame everything as items to verify with the destination-state DMV. Follow the SafeCopy avoid list.": "勿陈述哪些州对特定签证类别发或勿发驾照,也勿列出具体接受个证件。一律按要向目的州 DMV 核实个事项来表述。请遵循 SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Document lists accepted by state DMVs for non-citizen license or state-ID applicants can differ from those accepted for U.S. citizens, and accepted combinations may vary by jurisdiction.": "各州 DMV 接受非公民申请驾照或州身份证所列个证件,可能搭美国公民勿一样,可接受个证件组合各司法管辖区也可能勿一样。",
        "Documents for proof of identity": "身份证明文件",
        "Done": "完成",
        "Driver's license": "驾照",
        "Driving across one or more state lines for travel.": "为出行驾车跨越一个或多个州界。",
        "Driving with coverage that does not meet destination-state minimums can create compliance and financial problems.": "保额未达目的州最低标准就上路,可能带来合规搭财务方面个问题。",
        "Drug screen requirements": "药物筛查要求",
        "Edit selections": "编辑选择",
        "Emissions testing requirement": "排放测试要求",
        "Employer policy": "雇主政策",
        "Employment Authorization": "工作授权",
        "Employment paperwork": "雇佣文件",
        "Endorsement requirements if already licensed": "如已持照,背书要求",
        "Endorsement, reciprocity, temporary permits, and continuing education requirements vary by state and profession.": "背书、互认、临时许可,搭继续教育要求因州因专业而异。",
        "Endorsement, reciprocity, temporary practice, and continuing education.": "背书、互认、临时执业,搭继续教育。",
        "Enhanced or REAL ID": "增强型或 REAL ID",
        "Establishing a new permanent residence in the destination state.": "在目的州建立新个永久住所。",
        "Eviction and late-fee rules": "驱逐搭滞纳金规则",
        "Example checklist categories": "示例清单类别",
        "Exploring options. Receive a broad overview checklist.": "在了解选项。收到一份总览性清单。",
        "F-1 OPT and STEM OPT specific. Use verify with the DSO and SEVP Portal guidance. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list (legal-conclusion phrasing and penalty-avoidance phrasing). Do not advise on a specific status outcome.": "F-1 OPT 搭 STEM OPT 专属。请用「向 DSO 搭 SEVP Portal 指引核实」。勿使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避清单(法律结论搭规避处罚个措辞)。勿对具体身份后果作建议。",
        "F-1 specific. Frame as verify with both DSOs and reference Study in the States or ICE materials. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "F-1 专属。请按向两边 DSO 核实并参考 Study in the States 或 ICE 资料来表述。勿使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "F-1 students on post-completion OPT or a STEM OPT extension generally use the SEVP Portal or work with their DSO to update physical and mailing address, employer information, and other personal data, typically within 10 days of a change. Unemployment-day limits during OPT continue to apply during and after a move.": "处于毕业后 OPT 或 STEM OPT 延期个 F-1 学生,一般通过 SEVP Portal 或者搭 DSO 配合,在变更之后通常 10 日内更新实际搭邮寄地址、雇主信息搭其他个人资料。OPT 期间个失业天数上限,搬场期间搭之后仍然继续适用。",
        "F-1, J-1, M-1, and Q specific. Frame as items to verify with IRS guidance and the employer. Do not state that a particular worker is exempt from FICA. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "F-1、J-1、M-1 搭 Q 专属。请按要向 IRS 指引搭雇主核实个事项来表述。勿陈述某员工免缴 FICA。勿使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Factors that may affect residency for tuition, taxes, licensing, benefits.": "可能影响学费、税务、执业资格、福利相关居住身份个因素。",
        "Failing to register on time may affect eligibility for federal benefits, federal jobs, and naturalization later, even though the requirement is federal. State DMV workflows can also trigger automatic registration, which applicants should understand before applying.": "未按辰光登记可能影响后续个联邦福利、联邦工作搭入籍资格,即便该要求来自联邦。州 DMV 流程也可能触发自动登记,申请人应当在申请之前先了解清楚。",
        "Family move": "家庭搬场",
        "Federal HealthCare.gov guidance describes a list of immigration statuses considered lawfully present for purposes of the Affordable Care Act marketplace, which includes many common nonimmigrant categories. These categories can purchase coverage without a five-year waiting period that applies in many Medicaid contexts.": "联邦 HealthCare.gov 指引列出了在 ACA 市场上被认为「合法居留」个移民身份清单,其中包括许多常见非移民类别。介些类别好购买保障,勿适用 Medicaid 许多场景下个五年等待期。",
        "Federal Medicaid and CHIP rules generally include a five-year waiting period for many qualified non-citizens after obtaining qualified status, with several federal exceptions. States may use an option that removes the waiting period for children and pregnant people, and some states cover certain groups with state funds.": "联邦 Medicaid 搭 CHIP 规则一般对许多取得合格身份个非公民,在取得身份之后设五年等待期,有若干联邦例外。各州好选择对儿童搭孕妇取消等待期,部分州还用州资金覆盖特定群体。",
        "Federal Medicare guidance generally describes eligibility for non-citizens who are lawfully admitted for permanent residence and have lived in the United States for five continuous years. Federal Medicaid rules for most nonimmigrants are narrower than for LPRs, with state-specific options for emergency Medicaid and for lawfully residing children and pregnant individuals.": "联邦 Medicare 指引一般描述,合法获得永久居留并连续居住美国五年个非公民,具备资格。对大多数非移民,联邦 Medicaid 规则比 LPR 更窄,各州对紧急 Medicaid 搭合法居留个儿童搭孕妇有自定选项。",
        "Federal REAL ID rules require evidence of lawful status, and many states issue a REAL ID to nonimmigrant visa holders only with an expiration date that does not extend past the I-94, the visa, or another underlying federal document. Implementation differs between states, and standard (non-REAL-ID) options may or may not be offered.": "联邦 REAL ID 规则要合法身份证明,许多州对非移民签证持有人发个 REAL ID,有效期勿超过 I-94、签证或其他底层联邦文件个截止日。各州个执行勿一样,标准(非 REAL ID)选项是否提供也勿一定。",
        "Federal SNAP, TANF, and similar programs apply a waiting period to many qualified non-citizens. Some states use state funds to operate replacement or supplemental programs that cover groups not eligible for the federal program, with differing rules.": "联邦 SNAP、TANF 搭类似项目对许多合格非公民设有等待期。部分州用州资金运行替代或补充项目,覆盖勿符合联邦项目资格个群体,规则也勿一样。",
        "Federal law": "联邦法律",
        "Federal law (INA section 265) generally directs non-citizens to report a change of address to USCIS within 10 days of moving, typically through Form AR-11 or the USCIS online change-of-address tool. The federal filing is separate from updating a state DMV record, an employer, a school, or the U.S. Postal Service.": "联邦法律(INA 第 265 条)一般要求非公民在搬场之后 10 日内向 USCIS 报告地址变更,一般通过 Form AR-11 或者 USCIS 在线地址变更工具。该联邦申报搭更新州 DMV 记录、雇主、学校或 USPS 是分开个。",
        "Federal law generally requires motor vehicle offices to offer voter registration to applicants, and forms are screened for citizenship attestations. Non-citizens generally are not eligible to register for federal elections, and a registration record can later create immigration complications.": "联邦法律一般要求机动车机构向申请人提供选民登记机会,表格中会核对公民身份声明。非公民一般勿符合参加联邦选举登记个资格,登记记录之后可能给移民事项带来复杂问题。",
        "Federal residency for tax purposes determines whether worldwide income is reported, which IRS forms apply, and how an interstate move's first and last year are filed at the federal level, separately from state residency rules.": "联邦税务居住身份决定是否要申报全球收入、适用哪些 IRS 表格,搭跨州搬场后第一年搭最后一年在联邦层面如何申报,介些跟州一级居住规则是分开个。",
        "Federal rules govern which immigration statuses can purchase coverage and receive financial help through the Affordable Care Act marketplace, and those rules have changed. State-based marketplaces and state-funded programs add another layer that can differ between origin and destination.": "联邦规则决定哪些移民身份好通过 ACA 市场购买保障搭获取财务补助,而且规则已经发生变化。州一级个市场搭州资金项目又多一层规则,出发州搭目的州之间可能勿一样。",
        "Federal tax authority": "联邦税务机关",
        "Federal tax authority general guidance": "联邦税务机关一般指引",
        "Filing Requirements, Residency, and Telecommuting FAQs": "申报要求、居住身份搭远程办公常见问题",
        "Flags risk levels so you know where to focus": "标出风险等级,好让侬晓得重点关注啥地方",
        "Florida Board of Governors page on residency for tuition purposes for the State University System. flbog.edu returns 403 to non-browser requests (Cloudflare); this is a known false negative.": "Florida Board of Governors 关于州立大学系统学费意义上居住身份个页面。flbog.edu 对非浏览器请求返回 403(Cloudflare);这是已知误判。",
        "Florida FLHSMV documentation page for nonimmigrant applicants for driver licenses and identification cards.": "Florida FLHSMV 面向非移民驾照搭身份证申请人个文件页面。",
        "Follow device language": "跟随设备语言",
        "For L-1, whether the new worksite is the same qualifying U.S. office described in the petition or a different one": "对 L-1 来讲,新工作地点是否同请愿中所述个符合资格美国办公室一致,还是另一处",
        "For L-1A, L-1B, and O-1 status, USCIS treats a move to a new worksite as a material change in some fact patterns and not others, depending on what the original petition described and whether the new location is consistent with the approved terms. The analysis follows the underlying petition, not LCA-based MSA rules.": "对 L-1A、L-1B 搭 O-1 身份,USCIS 在某些情形下把换工作地点视为重大变更,某些情形下勿是,取决于原始请愿是怎么描述个,搭新地点是否符合已批准个条款。分析以底层请愿为准,而勿是基于 LCA 个 MSA 规则。",
        "For O-1, whether the new venue, event, engagement, or agent arrangement falls within the approved petition scope": "对 O-1 来讲,新个场所、活动、聘约或代理安排是否落在已批准请愿个范围之内",
        "For federal tax purposes, a non-citizen is generally treated as a resident alien if they meet the Substantial Presence Test or hold lawful permanent resident status, with separate rules in IRS Publication 519 for exempt individuals (such as certain F-1, J-1, M-1, and Q students and scholars) whose days of presence may not count.": "在联邦税务上,非公民如符合 Substantial Presence Test,或者持合法永久居民身份,一般被视为 resident alien;IRS Publication 519 对豁免个人(比如某些 F-1、J-1、M-1 搭 Q 类别个学生搭学者)有单独规则,他们个居留日数可能勿计入。",
        "For nursing specifically, how the destination state treats primary state of residency under the Nurse Licensure Compact for a non-citizen who declares either the country of origin or the compact state, and any credentials-evaluation requirement (for example, CGFNS) for internationally educated applicants": "具体到护理:目的州对非公民按护士执照联盟申报原籍国或者联盟州为主要居住州个情况怎么处理,搭对国际教育背景申请人是否要学历评估(比如 CGFNS)",
        "Form AR-11 paper version posted on uscis.gov.": "uscis.gov 上发布个 Form AR-11 纸质版。",
        "Frame AR-11 as a federal reporting step to verify, not a guarantee of status. Do not state that any specific status category is or is not covered without source. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list (legal-conclusion phrasing such as the i-word, the p-words, and penalty-avoidance phrasing). Direct readers to consult a licensed immigration attorney for status-specific guidance.": "请把 AR-11 表述成一个要核实个联邦报告步骤,而勿是身份个担保。在缺少来源个情况下,勿陈述某身份类别是否被覆盖。勿使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避清单(法律结论措辞、相关词,搭规避处罚个措辞)。引导读者就身份相关问题咨询持证移民律师。",
        "Frame as a federal requirement that may apply, with a nonimmigrant exception that may apply based on continuous valid status. Do not state that any specific person is or is not required to register. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "请按可能适用个联邦要求来表述,并说明在连续有效身份基础上可能适用非移民例外。勿陈述任何具体个人是否要登记。勿使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Frame as items to verify in IRS Publication 519 and with a qualified tax preparer. Do not state a person is a dual-status filer for a particular year. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "请按要向 IRS Publication 519 搭合格税务代办人员核实个事项来表述。勿陈述某人在特定年份属于双重身份申报人。勿使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Frame as items to verify with CMS and the destination-state Medicaid agency. Federal rules have changed and may continue to change. Do not state a person is or is not eligible. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "请按要向 CMS 搭目的州 Medicaid 机构核实个事项来表述。联邦规则已发生变化,也可能继续变化。勿陈述某人是否具备资格。勿使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Frame as items to verify with IRS Publication 519 and a tax preparer. Do not state a person is or is not a resident alien for federal tax purposes. Use may apply and rules differ by jurisdiction. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "请按要向 IRS Publication 519 搭税务代办人员核实个事项来表述。勿陈述某人在联邦税务上是否属于 resident alien。请用「可能适用」搭「各司法管辖区个规则不一样」。勿使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Frame as items to verify with the DSO or J-1 sponsor and Study in the States or ICE guidance. This item is specific to F-1, M-1, and J-1 status. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list (legal-conclusion phrasing and penalty-avoidance phrasing).": "请按要向 DSO 或 J-1 主办方,搭 Study in the States 或 ICE 指引核实个事项来表述。该项专属于 F-1、M-1 搭 J-1 身份。勿使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避清单(法律结论搭规避处罚个措辞)。",
        "Frame as items to verify with the current HealthCare.gov or state-based marketplace lists. Do not state any specific category is or is not on the lawfully present list, since federal rules have changed. Avoid the iOS SafeCopy avoid-list.": "请按要向当前 HealthCare.gov 或州一级市场清单核实个事项来表述。由于联邦规则已发生变化,勿陈述任何具体类别是否在合法居留清单上。勿使用 iOS SafeCopy 回避清单。",
        "Full disclaimer:": "完整免责声明:",
        "General information only. Not legal advice. Verify with official sources.": "仅供一般参考。勿是法律建议。请向官方来源核实。",
        "General information only. Verify with the relevant official source. Not legal advice.": "仅供一般参考。请向相关官方来源核实。勿是法律建议。",
        "Generate checklist": "生成清单",
        "Generated:": "生成辰光:",
